Evaluate genotypic frequencies at the adult run timing marker Omy_RAD15709-53 on chromosome 28 across contemporary samples collected in the years 2015 - 2019 (Fig 5).

##drop old collections 2000 - 2006##
contemp_full_markerset <- full_markerset %>%
  filter(! c(Year_Collected == "2000" | Year_Collected == "2003" | Year_Collected == "2006"))

Subset the dataframe to the sampling metadata and the Omy_RAD15709-53 marker.

omy_53 <- contemp_full_markerset[, c(1:27, 176)]   ##Grab metadata in columns 1:27 and the marker Omy_RAD15709-53 in column 176

Put the rows of the dataframe in order according to the location number.

##put rows in order of location number##
omy_53<-omy_53[order(as.numeric(as.character(omy_53$location_number))), ]

##Set order of locations##
omy_53$location_code<-factor(omy_53$location_code, levels = unique(omy_53$location_code))

Calculate genotypic frequencies for early (EE), heterozygous (EL), and late (LL) genotypes.

ws_summary <- omy_53 %>%
  group_by(location_code) %>%
  summarize(n = n(), EE = sum(`Omy_RAD15709-53` == "AA") / n, EL = sum(`Omy_RAD15709-53` == "GA") / n, LL = sum(`Omy_RAD15709-53` == "GG") / n, Missing = sum(`Omy_RAD15709-53` == "00") / n)

ws_summary %<>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(EE, EL, LL, Missing))

  scale_fill_manual(values = c("coral3", "gold2", "steelblue4", "gray70"), name = "Genotype") +

Evaluate genotype frequencies at seven adult run timing markers on chromosome 28 across contemporary samples collected in the years 2015 - 2019 (Supplementary Figure 3). Note, I think this is clunky but necessarily so. Each marker has different genotypes (e.g., AA, TT, CC, GG) that are associated with early or late return timing. Consequently, need to write conditions for each marker. Prepare dataframes for each marker.

Calculate genotype frequencies for each marker based on their unique polarization.

locus_1<-Chr28_1 %>%   ##Chr28_11667578##
  group_by(location_code) %>%
  summarize(n = n(), EE = sum(Chr28_11667578 == "TT") / n, EL = sum(Chr28_11667578 == "TC") / n, LL = sum(Chr28_11667578 == "CC") / n, Missing = sum(Chr28_11667578 == "00") / n)
locus_1 %<>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(EE, EL, LL, Missing))
locus_1$locus<-rep("Chr28_11667578", times = nrow(locus_1))
